review_blob: Often drink it. Great taste while still being quite light. An unsung hero of irish beers
Worst beer i have ever tasted.Drank it at lake Bled in Slovenia, tasted like it was watered down with sparkling water. Disgraceful

very average beer. I work as a barman and it is the flattest beer to pour, the head disintegrates within a minute of pouring. Tastes nothing special as well. Much better beers to taste then this one. Not bad at best really

Much heavier stout than Guinness. Very creamy head, with a slightly sweet aftertaste, which distinguishes itself from other stouts ive tried. great value as well, usually around 3.70 a pint. Definetly worth every penny and more
Great to drink on a summers day. Really depends if im in the mood for something that sweet. Certainly the best apple cider around
worst beer available in Ireland. Full of chemicals, tastes like watered down lager. Just goes to show what good advertising can do

love guinness. Although a lot depends on how it is poured, which greatly effects its consistency. Particularly the second pour, a lot of people think it is better to push the tap forward for this, which it is not. it is better to top up the pint by pulling the tap towards you, as it gives a grater flavour and creamier pint.

definetly my favourite lager beer from a can, great taste, better than anything else from a can. and its very cheap too! i cant believe people are so harsh on this beer, you cant say that something like heineken or budweiser is better. its great on draft too (staropramen).
